<body lang=EN-IN style='tab-interval:36.0pt;word-wrap:break-word'>

<div class=WordSection1>

<div class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>

<hr size=2 width="100%" align=center>

</span></div>

<h1><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Forge India
Workspace - Mobile Application Documentation<o:p></o:p></span></h1>

<p>Welcome to the comprehensive technical and operational guide for the <strong>Forge
India Workspace Mobile Application</strong>. This document outlines the mobile
architecture, core application features, technologies utilized, and user
workflows designed for team collaboration on the go.</p>

<p>The mobile application acts as the portable counterpart to the web
workspace, specializing in high-fidelity Unified Communications (Video
Conferencing and Chat) while maintaining strict enterprise security.</p>

<div class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>

<hr size=2 width="100%" align=center>

</span></div>

<h2><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Technologies Used<o:p></o:p></span></h2>

<p>The Forge India Workspace Mobile Application is engineered for
cross-platform performance using modern frameworks:</p>

<ul type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
     mso-list:l5 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list 36.0pt'><strong><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Core Framework</span></strong><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>: React Native &amp;
     Expo SDK (Cross-platform iOS and Android).<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
     mso-list:l5 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list 36.0pt'><strong><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Styling</span></strong><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>: Tailwind CSS (via </span><span
     class=SpellE><code><span style='font-size:10.0pt'>twrnc</span></code></span><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'> for native compilation)
     allowing consistent design language with the web application.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
     mso-list:l5 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list 36.0pt'><strong><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Real-Time Communication</span></strong><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>: </span><code><span
     style='font-size:10.0pt'>react-native-<span class=SpellE>webrtc</span></span></code><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'> (Video/Audio streams),
     Socket.io-client (<span class=SpellE>Signaling</span> and Chat).<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
     mso-list:l5 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list 36.0pt'><strong><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Hardware Integrations</span></strong><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>: </span><code><span
     style='font-size:10.0pt'>expo-<span class=SpellE>av</span></span></code><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'> (Audio session and
     speaker routing), </span><code><span style='font-size:10.0pt'>expo-camera</span></code><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'> (Device cameras).<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
     mso-list:l5 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list 36.0pt'><strong><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Backend</span></strong><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>: Integrates with the
     central Node.js/<span class=SpellE>Fastify</span> server and MongoDB
     infrastructure.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
</ul>

<div class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>

<hr size=2 width="100%" align=center>

</span></div>

<h2><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></h2>

<h2><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></h2>

<h2><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></h2>

<h2><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></h2>

<h2><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></h2>

<h2><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></h2>

<h2><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>1. Meetings (Video
Conferencing)<o:p></o:p></span></h2>

<p>The core offering of the mobile application is the highly optimized WebRTC
Meetings experience.</p>

<h3><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Deep Dive: Core
Functions &amp; Capabilities<o:p></o:p></span></h3>

<ul type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
     mso-list:l2 level1 lfo2;tab-stops:list 36.0pt'><strong><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Native WebRTC
     Integration</span></strong><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>:
     Leverages low-level WebRTC bindings for hardware-accelerated video
     decoding and low-latency audio transmission over mobile networks.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
     mso-list:l2 level1 lfo2;tab-stops:list 36.0pt'><strong><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Adaptive UI &amp;
     Scrollable Grids</span></strong><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>:
     The mobile interface utilizes flexible </span><span class=SpellE><code><span
     style='font-size:10.0pt'>ScrollView</span></code></span><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'> components to
     gracefully handle large participant counts (gallery view) without freezing
     or overflowing smaller screens.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
     mso-list:l2 level1 lfo2;tab-stops:list 36.0pt'><strong><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Advanced Audio
     Management</span></strong><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>:
     Background audio and interruption handling are strictly controlled using
     Expo AV to ensure call audio persists cleanly, even if the device screen
     locks.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
     mso-list:l2 level1 lfo2;tab-stops:list 36.0pt'><strong><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Host Controls</span></strong><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>: Full suite of
     moderation features accessible directly from the mobile app. Hosts can
     mute all participants, lock rooms, admit guests from a waiting room, and
     transfer presenter privileges.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
     mso-list:l2 level1 lfo2;tab-stops:list 36.0pt'><strong><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Local Screen Sharing</span></strong><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>: Native screen
     capturing allowing mobile users to broadcast their entire phone screen to
     the meeting room.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
</ul>

<h3><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>End-to-End User
Workflow<o:p></o:p></span></h3>

<ol start=1 type=1>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
     mso-list:l4 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list 36.0pt'><strong><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Joining a Call</span></strong><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>: Users open the app and
     paste a secure Room ID (or tap a deep link) to immediately enter the
     meeting lobby.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
     mso-list:l4 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list 36.0pt'><strong><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>In-Call Engagement</span></strong><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>: Inside the meeting,
     users can toggle their camera and microphone, flip between front and
     back-facing cameras, and view the active speaker dynamically highlighted.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
     mso-list:l4 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list 36.0pt'><strong><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Navigating Participants</span></strong><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>: Users can swipe
     through the vertical grid of participant tiles or pin a specific user
     (such as a presenter) to maximize their video feed on the screen.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
     mso-list:l4 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list 36.0pt'><strong><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Moderation (As Host)</span></strong><span
     style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>: A host taps the
     &quot;Host Controls&quot; tab to enforce room lock, preventing
     unauthorized attendees from joining late.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
</ol>

<div class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>

<hr size=2 width="100%" align=center>

</span></div>

<h2><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></h2>

<h2><span style='mso-no-proof:yes'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id="_x0000_t75"
